commentTextItems.html: yes he can ! lofts it over long off, onto the moto-cross track

commentPostTextItems.html: So Cheema finshes it in fine style, with a huge six over long off, Canada has taken a 1-0 lead in the series, a good all round performance in the field by them.
Man of the Match goes to Khurram Chohan for his spell of 4 for 26

commentTextItems.html: no one on the long on boundary, big chase for short mid wicket

commentPostTextItems.html: Can Cheema finish it with a six

commentTextItems.html: pulls it to the square leg

milestones.description: Rizwan Cheema has broken the record for most sixes (21) in ODIs for CAN, going past John Davison's 20

stories.title: Chohan sets up crushing win
stories.subTitle: Canada v Kenya, 1st ODI, Toronto
stories.summary: It was a no-contest at the Maple Leaf North West Ground as Kenya crashed to 113 and lost heavily by nine wickets to the hosts Canada in a match which lasted just 49.3 overs

image.caption: Rizwan Cheema lofts the ball on his way to an unbeaten 76
